Lagos – RB Leipzig of Germany youngster, Naby Keita has admitted that the 2018 FIFA World Cup in Russia will be a tough one for Africa representatives. Nigeria, Egypt, Tunisia, Morocco and Senegal are representing the continent of Africa at the World Cup, which kicks off on June 14 to end on July 15. Keita, who is set for a summer move to Liverpool FC of England, however predicted that the Super Eagles of Nigeria and at least one other African team will get to the semifinals. While also pointing out that no one should rule out the Pharaohs of Egypt, Desert Warriors of Tunisia, Atlas of Morocco and the Teranga Lions of Senegal at Russia 2018, Keita said he believes that the Super Eagles have a stronger depth and capacity to shoulder Africa’s hope for a historic outing. It will be recalled that only Cameroon, Senegal and Ghana made huge impacts in reaching the quarterfinals of the World Cup in 1990, 2002 and 2010, but Keita further attested that African teams have learnt from past flaws – and believes they will reach the last four at Russia 2018. Keita opined: “It will be a tough tournament for African teams but the good thing is that they have learnt from past mistakes. “I know Nigeria will lead by example and we will definitely have at least two teams in the semis of the competition. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 